    <item rdf:about="https://www.tina4.com/documentation/doku.php?id=tina4:tutorials:build-class-with-db-access&amp;rev=1622183585&amp;do=diff">
        <dc:format>text/html</dc:format>
        <dc:date>2021-05-28T08:33:05+00:00</dc:date>
        <dc:creator>Anonymous (anonymous@undisclosed.example.com)</dc:creator>
        <title>tina4:tutorials:build-class-with-db-access</title>
        <link>https://www.tina4.com/documentation/doku.php?id=tina4:tutorials:build-class-with-db-access&amp;rev=1622183585&amp;do=diff</link>
        <description>Class with database access

Any class that extends \Tina4\Data will have a database variable $this-&gt;DBA to access the database from.


class MyData extends \Tina4\Data {
  function getSomething() {
    return $this-&gt;DBA-&gt;select (&quot;*&quot;)-&gt;from(&quot;table&quot;)-&gt;asArray();
  } 
}</description>
    </item>
    <item rdf:about="https://www.tina4.com/documentation/doku.php?id=tina4:tutorials:connect-to-database&amp;rev=1622183286&amp;do=diff">
