        <dc:creator>Anonymous (anonymous@undisclosed.example.com)</dc:creator>
        <title>tina4:tutorials:connect-to-database</title>
        <link>https://www.tina4.com/documentation/doku.php?id=tina4:tutorials:connect-to-database&amp;rev=1622183286&amp;do=diff</link>
        <description>Connect to a database

Three database engines are currently supported. The global variable $DBA is used from index.php to establish a database connection.  Adding a date format is optional.

SQLite
 global $DBA;
 $DBA = new \Tina4\DataSQLite3(&quot;test.db&quot;, &quot;&quot;, &quot;&quot;, &quot;Y-m-d&quot;);</description>
    </item>
